<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="realloc" id="realloc">realloc</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="cpp code cpp"><span class="co2">#include &lt;cstdlib&gt;</span>
&nbsp;
<span class="kw4">void</span> <span class="sy2">*</span><span class="kw3">realloc</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">void</span> <span class="sy2">*</span>ptr, <span class="kw4">size_t</span> size <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
Reallocates the given area of memory. The contents of the area remain unchanged up to the lesser of the new and old sizes. If the area is expanded, the contents of the new part of the array are undefined.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT1 SECTION "realloc" [1-301] -->
<h3 class="sectionedit2"><a name="parameters" id="parameters">Parameters</a></h3>
<div class="level3">

<p>

<code>ptr</code> - pointer to the memory area to be reallocated. It must be previously returned from <code>malloc</code> or <code>calloc</code> otherwise the results are undefined.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT2 SECTION "Parameters" [302-476] -->
<h3 class="sectionedit3"><a name="return_value" id="return_value">Return value</a></h3>
<div class="level3">

<p>

pointer to the newly allocated area or NULL if there is not enough memory or an error has occurred. It must be deallocated with <a href="free" class="wikilink1" title="memory:c:free">free</a>
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT3 SECTION "Return value" [477-636] -->
<h3 class="sectionedit4"><a name="see_also" id="see_also">See also</a></h3>
<div class="level3">

<p>

<a href="calloc" class="wikilink1" title="memory:c:calloc">calloc</a>, <a href="free" class="wikilink1" title="memory:c:free">free</a>, <a href="malloc" class="wikilink1" title="memory:c:malloc">malloc</a>
</p>

</div>
